BT /F2 12 Tf 54 738.00 Td (Header comment) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 715.00 Td (The top comment explains a very important ESP8266 limitation:) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 696.00 Td (Both sensors are UART devices at 9600 baud, but the ESP8266 has only one full) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 683.00 Td (hardware UART available, and this project keeps it for USB logging/flashing.) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 664.00 Td (So the sensors use `SoftwareSerial`, which is "bit-banged" serial. Bit-banged) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 651.00 Td (serial is implemented in software, so it is timing-sensitive and can reliably) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 638.00 Td (listen to only one port at a time.) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 619.00 Td (That is why the firmware uses a state machine:) Tj ET
BT /F3 8.5 Tf 54 596.00 Td (PMS_LISTEN -> CO2_WAIT -> IDLE -> next cycle) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 575.00 Td (It listens to the particle sensor, then asks the CO2 sensor, then waits until) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 562.00 Td (the next 5-second cycle.) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 543.00 Td (The comment also explains why the TFT is redrawn during hand-off moments.) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 530.00 Td (Display SPI writes can be long bursts, and those bursts could interfere with) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 517.00 Td (SoftwareSerial timing if they happen while receiving PMS bytes.) Tj ET
