BT /F1 10 Tf 54 712.00 Td (10. The system idles until the 5-second interval is up.) Tj ET
BT /F2 14 Tf 54 685.00 Td (15. Why the Code Is Split This Way) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 658.00 Td (The split is clean and intentional:) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 639.00 Td (- `main.cpp` owns orchestration and timing.) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 626.00 Td (- `config.h` owns hardware/timing settings.) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 613.00 Td (- `pms5003.*` owns PMS5003 protocol parsing.) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 600.00 Td (- `mhz19.*` owns MH-Z19E protocol commands and parsing.) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 587.00 Td (- `aqi.*` owns AQI domain logic.) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 574.00 Td (- `ui.*` owns display rendering.) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 555.00 Td (This is similar to separating a web app into:) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 536.00 Td (- config) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 523.00 Td (- API clients) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 510.00 Td (- business/domain logic) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 497.00 Td (- state orchestration) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 484.00 Td (- UI components) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 465.00 Td (The difference is that firmware code must also manage hardware timing,) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 452.00 Td (byte-level protocols, limited RAM, and display redraw cost.) Tj ET
BT /F2 14 Tf 54 425.00 Td (16. Important Firmware Patterns Used) Tj ET
BT /F2 12 Tf 54 392.00 Td (Non-blocking state machine) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 369.00 Td (The code does not sit inside long `delay\(\)` calls waiting for sensors. Instead,) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 356.00 Td (it checks available bytes and timeouts on each `loop\(\)` pass.) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 337.00 Td (This keeps the firmware responsive to button presses and serial input.) Tj ET
BT /F2 12 Tf 54 312.00 Td (Validate before trusting sensor data) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 289.00 Td (Both sensor drivers check frame shape and checksum before updating stored data.) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 276.00 Td (This is important because serial bytes can be corrupted.) Tj ET
BT /F2 12 Tf 54 251.00 Td (Use timestamps instead of blocking waits) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 228.00 Td (The code uses:) Tj ET
BT /F3 8.5 Tf 54 205.00 Td (now - phaseStart > TIMEOUT) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 184.00 Td (This is the standard Arduino pattern for timeouts.) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 165.00 Td (It is also safer than comparing absolute future times because `millis\(\)` will) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 152.00 Td (eventually overflow. Unsigned subtraction keeps working across overflow for) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 139.00 Td (interval checks.) Tj ET
BT /F2 12 Tf 54 114.00 Td (Separate data from rendering) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 91.00 Td (`UiModel` decouples measurement state from drawing. This makes the UI code) Tj ET
BT /F1 10 Tf 54 78.00 Td (easier to change without touching sensor protocol code.) Tj ET
endstream
endobj
